        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Office of<lb/>
                <del>J. MAY</del> &#38; H. S. FRIEDMAN.<lb/>
                Late TROUTMAN&#44; MAY &#38; CO.<lb/>
                <del>18 North Third Street.</del><lb/>
                312 Market Str.<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia&#44; Oct. 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1879<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>The Literary Commee. Y. M. H. A.<lb/> instructed me sometime ago to communi<lb/>cate with you in regard to the delivery<lb/> of a lecture&#44; by you&#44; on some Jewish topic&#44;<lb/> History or Literature&#44; at one of the Infor<lb/>mals&#44; during this season &#40;Oct. to May 1880&#41;.<lb/></p>
            <p>I have been anxious to do myself<lb/> the honor of a personal interview<lb/> with you but circumstances of one kind or<lb/> another prevented my doing so &#38;<lb/> fearing&#44; lest delay in doing my duty<lb/> may prevent your acceptance I hasten<lb/> to invite you to honor us with<lb/> an address as above indicated.<lb/>  Your past efforts having proved<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>a very great treat&#44; I hope to<lb/> be advised of your acceptance.<lb/>  With my kindest regards for yourself&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>I am&#44; sir<lb/>
                yours very Respectfully<lb/>
                H. S. Friedman<lb/>
                Chrmn Literary Commee.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. s. Morais<lb/>
                Philada.<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
